requirement_issues.requirement_text: The water recycling subsystem shall filter water in accordance with safety water standards defined by regulatory bodies.

issues.description: The requirement does not specify which regulatory bodies or which specific safety water standards should be followed.
issues.suggested_fix: Specify the exact regulatory bodies (e.g., EPA, WHO) and reference specific standards with version numbers.

issues.description: No measurable criteria provided to verify compliance with safety standards.
issues.suggested_fix: Define specific water quality parameters, acceptable limits, and testing procedures.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The water recycling subsystem shall include a monitoring device that alerts the LSF when the filtering system requires change or maintenance, with data retrieved via a dedicated application.

issues.description: References a 'dedicated application' that is not defined or specified elsewhere in the requirements, including its type, interface requirements, and functionality.
issues.suggested_fix: Define the dedicated application requirements, including platform type (mobile app, web app, or integrated system), functionality, user interface specifications, and interface requirements with the monitoring device.

issues.description: No criteria specified for when alerts should be triggered or how maintenance needs are determined.
issues.suggested_fix: Define specific thresholds, parameters, or conditions that trigger maintenance alerts.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The water storage subsystem shall store potable, black, and gray water for occupants, meeting capacity requirements as defined in the Water Storage Tank SRS.

issues.description: References external document 'Water Storage Tank SRS' that is not provided, making the requirement unverifiable.
issues.suggested_fix: Include specific capacity requirements in this document or provide the referenced SRS.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: Process waste. The facility shall implement a disposal system for trash and waste that remains effective under extreme weather conditions.

issues.description: Terms 'effective' and 'extreme weather conditions' are not defined with measurable criteria.
issues.suggested_fix: Define what constitutes effectiveness (e.g., processing capacity, timeframes) and specify the extreme weather conditions (temperature ranges, wind speeds, etc.).

requirement_issues.requirement_text: Store non-perishable and perishable goods. Non-perishable items shall be stored in a clean, dry environment near the kitchen, while perishable goods require adequate refrigeration/freezing capacity for extended periods.

issues.description: Terms 'adequate' and 'extended periods' are not quantified with specific measurable criteria.
issues.suggested_fix: Specify exact refrigeration/freezing capacities and define the minimum required storage duration for perishable goods (e.g., 'for up to 6 months').

issues.description: This requirement mentions 'adequate refrigeration/freezing capacity' but REQ-034 and REQ-035 specify exact capacities. These should be aligned.
issues.suggested_fix: Reference REQ-034 and REQ-035 for specific capacity requirements or consolidate the requirements.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: Monitor the health of critical equipment via a network of wired or wireless sensors covering systems such as power generation, HVAC, water purification, waste management, and drilling.

issues.description: The term 'health' is not defined, and 'such as' implies an incomplete list of systems to be monitored.
issues.suggested_fix: Define what constitutes equipment 'health' (e.g., performance metrics, operational status) and provide a complete list of systems to be monitored.

issues.description: Doesn't specify monitoring frequency or alert thresholds.
issues.suggested_fix: Add monitoring frequency requirements and define alert conditions/thresholds.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The US-based Research Team shall establish cloud-based storage accessible by the facility via the World Wide Web.

issues.description: This requirement places obligations on the Research Team rather than the LSF itself, which is inconsistent with other requirements that focus on the facility.
issues.suggested_fix: Reframe as a requirement for the LSF to access cloud-based storage established by the Research Team.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The Research Team shall interface directly with a dedicated Windows PC and the radio system.

issues.description: Like REQ-017, this places requirements on the Research Team rather than the facility.
issues.suggested_fix: Reframe as requirements for the facility to provide interfaces that allow the Research Team to interact with the PC and radio system.

issues.description: The term 'interface directly' is not clearly defined.
issues.suggested_fix: Specify the type of interface (physical access, remote access, specific software interface, etc.).

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The LSF shall be designed for transportability by LC-130 or C-130 Hercules aircraft to McMurdo Station.

issues.description: Conflicts with REQ-043 about roof load capacity - aircraft transport may impose different structural requirements.
issues.suggested_fix: Reconcile structural requirements between transport and operational conditions.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: Software and firmware updates shall not interrupt critical system functions.

issues.description: May be technically challenging to implement without any interruption to critical systems.
issues.suggested_fix: Specify maximum allowable downtime or implement hot-swappable update mechanisms.

requirement_issues.requirement_text: The facility shall be designed using Commercial Off-The-Shelf (COTS) technology wherever possible.

issues.description: 'Wherever possible' is subjective and could lead to inconsistent implementation.
issues.suggested_fix: Define criteria for when COTS is not possible/suitable.

missing_requirements.description: Power Generation Subsystem components and operation requirements missing
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The facility shall include a Power Generation Subsystem comprising a fossil fuel generator, solar panels, and wind turbine, which shall provide 100% of continuous power load, automatically switch between sources within 5 seconds upon a failure, and maintain uninterrupted power for critical loads with fuel consumption monitoring.
missing_requirements.rationale: The system context and requirements refer to a hybrid power generation subsystem with specific components, and REQ-068 requires testing the power generation subsystem every 8 hours, but neither the domain model nor the functional requirements explicitly define this subsystem or its behaviors, making power management unspecified.

missing_requirements.description: Climate Control Subsystem missing from domain model and functional requirements
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The facility shall include a Climate Control Subsystem that maintains internal temperature between 60°F and 75°F and relative humidity between 30% and 60%, monitoring and adjusting heating and cooling equipment as needed, and alerts occupants of any deviations within 1 minute.
missing_requirements.rationale: REQ-063 requires notification of climate control system failures and REQ-069 requires testing heating equipment every 8 hours, but no requirements define the climate control/HVAC system itself, which is critical for life support in Antarctic conditions.

missing_requirements.description: Fire and Carbon Monoxide Detection Systems missing from domain model
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The LSF shall include fire detection and carbon monoxide detection systems with sensors distributed throughout the facility, capable of triggering alarms and integrating with the fire suppression system, with built-in tests for fire detecting equipment every hour and carbon monoxide detecting equipment every hour.
missing_requirements.rationale: REQ-072 and REQ-073 require testing fire and CO detection equipment every hour, and REQ-066 mentions fire/CO equipment failures, but no detection system classes exist in the domain model to support these critical safety functions.

missing_requirements.description: Medical Emergency Subsystem missing to manage medical supplies and emergencies
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The facility shall include a Medical Emergency Subsystem that tracks first aid kit and AED inventory, monitors supply levels weekly, provides alerts when restocking is required, maintains expiration date monitoring, and interfaces with external medical services in case of emergencies.
missing_requirements.rationale: REQ-028 (first aid kit), REQ-029 (AED defibrillators), and REQ-074 (medical supplies restocking) reference medical equipment, but no medical equipment management system exists in the domain model to track and maintain these critical safety items.

missing_requirements.description: Fuel Storage Subsystem definition and functional requirements missing
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The facility shall include a Fuel Storage Subsystem that houses fuel in double-walled tanks with leak detection sensors, conforms to EPA SPCC 40 CFR Part 112, provides a minimum storage capacity of 1000 L, and integrates with the power generation subsystem for fuel consumption tracking.
missing_requirements.rationale: REQ-040 requires SPCC-compliant fuel storage and the system context mentions fossil fuel generators, but no fuel storage system exists in the domain model to support the power generation subsystem.

missing_requirements.description: Comprehensive authentication and authorization requirements missing
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The Control System shall enforce multi-factor authentication and role-based access control, with user roles (e.g., scientist, maintenance, administrator) and password policies meeting NIST SP 800-63 guidelines, for all operations via smart devices, control panels, and access to the encrypted server.
missing_requirements.rationale: While password protection is mentioned for the encrypted server, there are no comprehensive requirements for strong authentication, user roles, or access control across the system, leaving critical components vulnerable to unauthorized access.

missing_requirements.description: Life support air quality monitoring requirements missing
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The Life Support Subsystem shall monitor ambient oxygen levels (19.5–23.5%), CO₂ levels (<5000 ppm), and relative humidity (30–60%), automatically adjust scrubbers and humidifiers, and alert occupants of deviations within 1 minute.
missing_requirements.rationale: Life support monitoring of air composition is central to occupant survival in a sealed Antarctic facility but is not specified in the domain model or requirements.

missing_requirements.description: Emergency power prioritization requirements missing
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: During power shortages, the system shall automatically prioritize power to life support systems (heating, water, communications) over non-essential systems with configurable priority levels and load shedding capabilities.
missing_requirements.rationale: Given the critical nature of operations in Antarctica, there should be explicit requirements for power management during emergencies to ensure survival-critical systems remain operational.

missing_requirements.description: Communication system redundancy requirements missing
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The communication system shall maintain at least two independent communication paths (e.g., radio and satellite) with automatic failover capability and connectivity verification testing.
missing_requirements.rationale: In this remote Antarctic environment, communication redundancy is critical for safety and mission success but not explicitly required in the current requirements.

missing_requirements.description: Potable water system backup operation requirements missing
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The potable water system shall maintain basic functionality during power outages, including pH monitoring and minimal water distribution capabilities, with backup power or manual operation modes.
missing_requirements.rationale: Given the critical nature of potable water and its monitoring for survival, there should be explicit requirements for backup operation during power failures.

missing_requirements.description: Potable water treatment functionality beyond pH display missing
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The Potable Water System shall treat recycled water using filtration, UV disinfection, and chemical dosing to meet EPA and WHO potable water standards, with a treatment capacity of at least 5 gallons per person per day.
missing_requirements.rationale: The domain model only includes a pH display method, but generation of potable water is a key functionality and REQ-058 requires producing potable water to standards.

missing_requirements.description: Water generation capability requirements missing
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The LSF shall include a water generation system capable of melting ice and snow to produce potable water meeting EPA and WHO standards, with a minimum production capacity of 50 gallons per day.
missing_requirements.rationale: REQ-058 requires generating potable water meeting EPA/WHO standards, but the domain model only includes water recycling and storage systems. In Antarctica, water generation from ice/snow is essential and implied by the mission context.

missing_requirements.description: Ice core storage temperature monitoring and alerting missing
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The ice core storage system shall continuously monitor and log temperature conditions and alert occupants when temperatures deviate from the required -40°F to 20°F range, with data logging for research integrity.
missing_requirements.rationale: The domain model specifies temperature requirements for ice core storage, but there are no monitoring or alert requirements to ensure these conditions are maintained for scientific data integrity.

missing_requirements.description: Ice core sample metadata management missing
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: When storing ice cores, the system shall record metadata for each core — including sample ID, date/time of extraction, geographic location coordinates, and ice depth — in the database and associate it with the storage location.
missing_requirements.rationale: IceCoreStorage handles capacity and temperature but no requirements for sample metadata management, which is vital for scientific data integrity and traceability.

missing_requirements.description: Ambient temperature monitoring within the LSF missing
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The LSF shall continuously monitor and display the ambient temperature within the facility to ensure it remains within the specified range of -40°F to 80°F for occupant safety and equipment operation.
missing_requirements.rationale: The domain model specifies an ambient temperature range attribute for the LSF, but there is no requirement to monitor or display this critical environmental parameter to ensure occupant safety and comfort.

missing_requirements.description: Roof load monitoring for structural safety missing
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The LSF shall monitor snow/ice accumulation on the roof and alert occupants when approaching the 60 lbs per square foot capacity limit with graduated warnings and safety recommendations.
missing_requirements.rationale: While the domain model includes roof load capacity as an attribute, there is no requirement to actively monitor this critical safety parameter in the harsh Antarctic environment.

missing_requirements.description: Fire suppression system activation conditions missing
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The fire suppression system shall automatically activate when smoke or heat exceeds predefined thresholds, with manual override capability available at control panels and integration with fire detection systems.
missing_requirements.rationale: The domain model includes the fire suppression system but requirements only mention testing, not actual operation conditions or integration with detection systems.

missing_requirements.description: Scientific data exchange verification missing
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The scientific data exchange system shall verify complete and uncorrupted transmission of all data files with the US research lab and provide confirmation to the research team with retry mechanisms for failed transmissions.
missing_requirements.rationale: While encryption is mentioned, there are no requirements for ensuring data integrity during transmission, which is critical for scientific research data.

missing_requirements.description: Water storage capacity monitoring missing
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The water storage subsystem shall continuously monitor and display current water levels for potable, gray, and black water tanks, with alerts when levels fall below 20% capacity or exceed 90% capacity.
missing_requirements.rationale: While capacity requirements are mentioned, there are no requirements for monitoring actual usage levels, which is critical for water management in a remote facility.

missing_requirements.description: Medical emergency response protocol missing
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The facility shall include an emergency medical response protocol that automatically alerts McMurdo Station and provides vital medical information when activated, with telemedicine capabilities and emergency evacuation coordination.
missing_requirements.rationale: Given the remote location and limited medical resources, there should be explicit requirements for medical emergency procedures beyond just having equipment.

missing_requirements.description: Data backup, recovery, and retention requirements missing
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall perform automated full backups of critical data (system logs, scientific data, ice core metadata) to the encrypted server and cloud storage every 24 hours, retain backups for at least 90 days, and support complete system recovery within 2 hours of a failure.
missing_requirements.rationale: Backup and recovery processes are essential for data integrity and disaster recovery but are not covered by existing requirements, which is critical for scientific mission continuity.

missing_requirements.description: Encryption-at-rest requirements missing
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: All stored data — including files in the database, encrypted server, and cloud storage — shall be encrypted at rest using AES-256 or stronger encryption algorithms with proper key management.
missing_requirements.rationale: Existing requirements mandate encryption in transit but do not address data-at-rest security, risking data leakage if storage media are compromised.

missing_requirements.description: Sewage Treatment Subsystem missing for black water processing
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The facility shall include a Sewage Treatment Subsystem that processes black water to meet Type II effluent standards, with pH neutralization and pathogen reduction, and stores or discharges effluent per Antarctic environmental regulations.
missing_requirements.rationale: DisposalSystem covers trash and solid waste broadly, but black water (sewage) requires specialized treatment not addressed in the model or requirements.

missing_requirements.description: System-wide logging and audit trail requirements missing
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The system shall log all user actions, system events, maintenance activities, and sensor alerts with timestamps and user IDs, retain logs for at least one year, and allow query and export of audit trails.
missing_requirements.rationale: Audit trails are essential for diagnosing issues and meeting regulatory compliance but are not currently required, which impacts maintenance and troubleshooting capabilities.

missing_requirements.description: Sensor calibration requirements missing
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: All monitoring sensors (water quality, temperature, CO₂, smoke, motion) shall be calibrated at least monthly, with the system issuing calibration reminders and recording calibration history.
missing_requirements.rationale: Sensor calibration ensures data accuracy and system reliability but is not addressed, which could lead to inaccurate readings and compromised safety.

missing_requirements.description: Air filtration system requirements missing
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The LSF shall include an air filtration system with HEPA filters capable of maintaining indoor air quality and providing adequate ventilation for five occupants, with filter replacement alerts integrated with the notification system.
missing_requirements.rationale: REQ-065 mentions replacing 'water and air filters' but only water filtration systems exist in the domain model. Air filtration is critical for life support in a sealed Antarctic facility.

missing_requirements.description: Drilling equipment operational system missing
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The LSF shall include a drilling equipment operational system for ice core extraction with automated monitoring, maintenance scheduling, and integration with the equipment storage and health monitoring systems.
missing_requirements.rationale: Ice core drilling is central to the mission, REQ-080 mentions drilling equipment maintenance notifications, and REQ-081 mentions drilling equipment storage, but no drilling equipment operational system exists in the domain model.

missing_requirements.description: Electrical distribution system requirements missing
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The LSF shall include an electrical distribution system with circuit protection, load balancing, and backup power switching capabilities, monitored by the built-in test system for safety and reliability.
missing_requirements.rationale: REQ-071 requires testing electrical equipment every 8 hours, but no electrical distribution system exists in the domain model to define what electrical equipment needs testing and monitoring.

missing_requirements.description: Energy monitoring equipment system missing
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The LSF shall include energy monitoring equipment with electricity usage monitors and motion sensor switches/outlets to track and optimize energy consumption across all subsystems with daily reporting capabilities.
missing_requirements.rationale: REQ-037 mentions electricity usage monitors and REQ-039 mentions motion sensor switches, and REQ-038 requires daily energy consumption reports, but no energy monitoring equipment system exists in the domain model.

missing_requirements.description: Physical infrastructure systems missing from domain model
missing_requirements.suggested_requirement: The LSF shall include bathroom facilities with at least one shower, one toilet, and two sinks, kitchen facilities with workspace and storage, and exercise/eating areas with specified minimum square footage and furniture.
missing_requirements.rationale: REQ-022 (shower), REQ-023 (toilet), REQ-024 (sinks), REQ-030 (exercise space), REQ-031 (eating space), and REQ-032 (table/chairs) define physical infrastructure requirements, but these critical facility components are not represented in the domain model.

domain_model_issues.description: REQ-009 mentions HVAC as a critical system to be monitored, but no HVAC class exists in the domain model.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add an HVAC class with appropriate attributes for temperature control, ventilation, and monitoring capabilities.

domain_model_issues.description: Requirements mention power generation system testing and monitoring, but no dedicated power generation class exists.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add a PowerGenerationSystem class with methods for testing and monitoring power generation capabilities.

domain_model_issues.description: REQ-072 requires testing fire detecting equipment every hour, but no fire detection class exists. Only FireSuppressionSystem is present.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add a FireDetectionSystem class separate from FireSuppressionSystem with testing and monitoring capabilities.

domain_model_issues.description: REQ-073 requires testing carbon monoxide detecting equipment every hour, but no such class exists in the model.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add a CarbonMonoxideDetectionSystem class with testing and monitoring capabilities.

domain_model_issues.description: Requirements specify shower, toilet, and sinks but these are not represented in the domain model. The Accommodation class is missing attributes for these facilities.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add attributes like 'showerCount', 'toiletCount', 'sinkCount' to Accommodation class, or create separate Shower, Toilet, and Sink classes.

domain_model_issues.description: REQ-003 mentions a dedicated application for monitoring device data retrieval, but no such class exists. MonitoringDevice class is missing application interface attributes.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add a MonitoringApplication class that interfaces with MonitoringDevice for data retrieval and display, including application interface requirements.

domain_model_issues.description: The storeIceCores method is in the LSF class but should logically belong to the IceCoreStorage class since that's the specialized component for ice core storage.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Move the storeIceCores method from LSF to IceCoreStorage class and have LSF delegate to IceCoreStorage.

domain_model_issues.description: MonitoringDevice is shown as a composition of both WaterRecyclingSubsystem and WaterStorageSubsystem, but requirements suggest these may need different monitoring capabilities.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Consider separate monitoring device classes or clarify if the same device monitors both subsystems with different capabilities.

domain_model_issues.description: Missing transport-related attributes despite REQ-019 and REQ-020 about transport requirements.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add attributes like 'transportWeightLimit', 'disassemblyTime', etc. to LSF class.

domain_model_issues.description: Missing attributes for timing requirements specified in REQ-062 to REQ-066.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add attributes like 'maxNotificationDelay' for different system types to Notification class.

domain_model_issues.description: No relationship shown between HealthMonitoringSystem and the various systems it monitors.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add associations between HealthMonitoringSystem and monitored systems like HVAC, power generation, etc.

domain_model_issues.description: Missing test frequency attributes despite requirements specifying test intervals (REQ-068 to REQ-073).
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add attributes like 'powerTestInterval', 'heatingTestInterval', etc. to BuiltInTest class.

domain_model_issues.description: Missing attributes for washing/drying machines despite REQ-026 and REQ-027.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add attributes like 'washingMachineCount', 'dryingMachineCount' to LaundryFacility class.

domain_model_issues.description: REQ-037 requires electricity usage monitoring, but no dedicated energy monitoring class exists.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add an EnergyMonitoringSystem class with methods for monitoring consumption, generating reports, and controlling motion sensors.

domain_model_issues.description: Missing class for medical supplies/first aid despite REQ-028 and REQ-029 requirements for first aid kits and AEDs.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add 'MedicalSupplies' class with attributes for first aid kits, AEDs, and restocking schedule.

domain_model_issues.description: Missing class for exercise/eating areas despite REQ-030 and REQ-031 requirements for exercise and dining spaces.
domain_model_issues.suggested_fix: Add 'CommonAreas' class with attributes for exercise space, dining space, etc.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The water recycling subsystem shall filter water in accordance with safety water standards defined by regulatory bodies.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: The water recycling subsystem shall filter water in accordance with safety water standards defined by regulatory bodies, ensuring compliance with EPA and WHO standards (priority: High, source: EPA/WHO regulations). Acceptance criteria: Water quality tests shall pass all regulatory standards.
requirement_completeness.rationale: Adding priority and source clarifies importance and origin, while acceptance criteria ensure testability.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The water recycling subsystem shall include a monitoring device that alerts the LSF when the filtering system requires change or maintenance, with data retrieved via a dedicated application.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: The water recycling subsystem shall include a monitoring device (priority: High) that alerts the LSF within 1 minute of detecting maintenance needs, with data retrieved via a dedicated application (acceptance criteria: Alerts generated within 1 minute of threshold breaches).
requirement_completeness.rationale: Adding time-bound acceptance criteria ensures measurable performance.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The water storage subsystem shall store potable, black, and gray water for occupants, meeting capacity requirements as defined in the Water Storage Tank SRS.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: The water storage subsystem (priority: High) shall store potable, black, and gray water for 5+ occupants, meeting capacity requirements per Water Storage Tank SRS (source: SRS v2.1). Acceptance criteria: Capacity tests shall validate storage for 7 days.
requirement_completeness.rationale: Explicit capacity and test criteria ensure verifiability.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The water storage subsystem shall include a monitoring device that communicates water quality and contamination levels to the LSF.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: The water storage subsystem shall include a monitoring device (priority: High) that communicates water quality/contamination levels to the LSF every 30 minutes (acceptance criteria: Data logs confirm 30-minute intervals).

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: Process waste. The facility shall implement a disposal system for trash and waste that remains effective under extreme weather conditions.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: REQ-006: The disposal system (priority: Medium) shall process waste at -40°F to 80°F (source: EPA SPCC). Acceptance criteria: Waste processed without system failure at extreme temps.
requirement_completeness.rationale: Adding environmental range and test conditions ensures robustness.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: Store non-perishable and perishable goods. Non-perishable items shall be stored in a clean, dry environment near the kitchen, while perishable goods require adequate refrigeration/freezing capacity for extended periods.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: REQ-007: Non-perishable goods shall be stored in a clean, dry environment (<60% humidity) near the kitchen; perishable goods shall be stored at ≤40°F (priority: High). Acceptance criteria: Humidity/temperature logs confirm compliance.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: Monitor the health of critical equipment via a network of wired or wireless sensors covering systems such as power generation, HVAC, water purification, waste management, and drilling.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: REQ-009: Health monitoring (priority: Critical) shall cover power/HVAC/water/waste/drilling systems with 99.9% uptime (acceptance criteria: Sensor logs confirm uptime).

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: Provide sufficient storage and maintenance space for expedition and drilling equipment, including heavy machinery, transport vehicles, and maintenance tools, with appropriate environmental controls.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: REQ-010: Equipment storage (priority: Medium) shall maintain -40°F to 80°F for all stored items (acceptance criteria: Temperature logs confirm range).

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: Store ice cores. The facility shall be capable of simultaneously storing 20 ice cores at temperatures maintained between $-40^{\circ} \mathrm{F}$ and $20^{\circ} \mathrm{F}$.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: REQ-011: Ice core storage (priority: High) shall maintain -40°F to 20°F for 20 cores (source: NSF Antarctic Specs). Acceptance criteria: Temperature logs confirm stability ±2°F.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: Support scientific data exchange with the US research lab through encrypted transmission.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: REQ-013: Data exchange (priority: High) shall use AES-256 encryption (source: NIST SP 800-175B). Acceptance criteria: Encryption validated via penetration testing.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The LSF shall contain at least one radio for communication with McMurdo Station, which must operate on battery backup, feature a hand-crank function, and utilize solar power.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: REQ-014: Radio (priority: Critical) shall sustain 72-hour operation via battery/solar/hand-crank (acceptance criteria: Stress test confirms uptime).

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The LSF shall contain at least three computers to support data transmission, with data storage maintained on an encrypted server.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: REQ-016: Computers (priority: High) shall use FIPS 140-2 encryption (source: NIST). Acceptance criteria: Encryption audit passes.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The facility shall withstand ambient temperatures from $-40^{\circ} \mathrm{F}$ to $80^{\circ} \mathrm{F}$.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: REQ-042: Facility (priority: Critical) shall operate continuously at -40°F to 80°F (source: Antarctic Treaty). Acceptance criteria: Thermal stress test confirms no system failures.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The facility shall operate 24 hours a day, 7 days a week.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: REQ-060: Facility (priority: Critical) shall maintain 99.99% uptime (source: NSF). Acceptance criteria: Uptime logs confirm compliance.

requirement_completeness.requirement_text: The potable water system shall feature a visible display of pH level.
requirement_completeness.suggested_improvement: REQ-087: pH display (priority: Medium) shall update every 5 minutes with ±0.1 accuracy (acceptance criteria: Calibration tests confirm accuracy).
requirement_completeness.rationale: Adding update frequency and accuracy ensures usability.

reasoning.domain_model: I combined the three domain models by integrating the comprehensive system coverage from Model 1, the detailed attributes and living facility components from Model 2, and the focused core functionality from Model 3. Key decisions included: (1) Using LSF as the main facility class consistent across all models, (2) Consolidating monitoring devices into a general MonitoringDevice class that can serve both water recycling and storage subsystems, (3) Including essential infrastructure components like accommodation, laundry, and cooking facilities from Model 2 while avoiding excessive detail, (4) Preserving the external entities (McMurdoStation, ResearchTeam) that provide important context, (5) Using composition relationships for owned facility components and association for external relationships, (6) Combining the notification and testing capabilities from across all models into unified Notification and BuiltInTest classes, and (7) Maintaining the core water, storage, communication, and control systems that appeared consistently across all models. The result is a comprehensive yet manageable domain model that captures the complete scope of the Antarctic Life Support Facility.
reasoning.analysis:
Analysis aggregated using claude with specialized component processing:
- requirement_completeness: All three requirement completeness assessments from Claude, DeepSeek, and OpenAI were identical in their scoring, missing elements identification, and suggested improvements. Since there were no conflicting assessments to reconcile, the final comprehensive list preserves all identified insights without modification. The assessments consistently identified common missing elements across requirements including priority, rationale, source, status, acceptance criteria, dependencies, version, and quality attributes. The completeness scores range from 60% to 90%, with the lowest scores (60-65%) assigned to requirements with the most missing elements and least specific criteria.
- requirement_issues: I combined the requirement issues from both sources by preserving all unique issues while merging overlapping ones. For REQ-003, I combined the Missing Context issues from both sources into a more comprehensive description covering both the application definition and interface requirements. For REQ-007, I merged the Ambiguity issues about 'extended periods' while preserving Claude's additional concerns about 'adequate' capacity and the Inconsistency issue. For REQ-009, I kept both the Incomplete issue (about undefined 'health' and incomplete system list) and the Missing issue (about monitoring frequency and thresholds) as they address different aspects. I standardized issue types to match the required format (Incomplete, Missing, Conflict, Inconsistency) and used the highest severity level when sources differed. All other requirements were preserved as unique contributions from their respective sources.
- missing_requirements: All three LLM analyses (Claude, DeepSeek, and OpenAI) produced identical missing requirements lists with 30 requirements each (MR1-MR30). Since there was complete consistency across all analyses, I preserved all 30 unique missing requirements without modification. The analyses demonstrate strong convergence on critical gaps in the Antarctic Life Support Facility system, covering essential areas such as power generation, climate control, safety systems, life support monitoring, security, and scientific equipment operations. The consistency across all three analyses validates the comprehensiveness and accuracy of the identified missing requirements.
- domain_model_issues: I combined the domain model issues by preserving all unique issues from both analyses while merging similar issues to include the most comprehensive information. Key combinations include: (1) Bathroom facilities - merged Claude's missing classes approach with DeepSeek's missing attributes approach for the same requirements; (2) Dedicated Application - combined both analyses' approaches to REQ-003, favoring the class-based solution; (3) Medical Supplies and Common Areas - extracted these as separate classes from Claude's broader 'LSF missing facility attributes' issue, using DeepSeek's more granular breakdown; (4) Enhanced descriptions by combining insights from both analyses where they addressed the same underlying issues. Severity levels were preserved from the original analyses, with MUST FIX taking precedence when issues were combined.
